Add an "Approve" quick-reply button to agent→human message rows in `public/app.js` and style it in `public/style.css`.

## What to build

For messages where `from_id !== 'human'` (i.e. sent by an agent to the human), add a small approve button that fires a `"Approved."` reply back to the agent.

### `public/app.js` — message row HTML

In `renderMessages()`, update the message row template for agent messages. After the `.message-content` div, add an actions row:

```javascript
const approveBtn = !fromHuman
  ? `<div class="message-actions">
       <button class="msg-approve-btn" data-to="${esc(m.from_id)}" data-priority="${m.priority}">✓ approve</button>
     </div>`
  : '';
```

And add it inside `.message-body`:
```html
<div class="message-content">...</div>
${approveBtn}
```

### `public/app.js` — wire the click

After morphdom renders, wire the approve buttons:
```javascript
messagesList.querySelectorAll('.msg-approve-btn').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const toId = btn.dataset.to;
    const priority = parseInt(btn.dataset.priority ?? '5', 10);
    btn.disabled = true;
    btn.textContent = '✓ sent';
    await fetch('/api/messages', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ to_id: toId, content: 'Approved.', priority }),
    });
  });
});
```

### `public/style.css`

```css
.message-actions { margin-top: 6px; }
.msg-approve-btn {
  font-size: 10px;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: none;
  color: var(--muted);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  font-family: inherit;
  align-self: auto;
}
.msg-approve-btn:hover:not(:disabled) { border-color: var(--idle); color: var(--idle); opacity: 1; }
.msg-approve-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: default; }
```

## Notes
- No backend changes needed — `POST /api/messages` already exists
- Button appears on all agent→human messages — it's a quick-reply shortcut
- After sending: button shows "✓ sent" and is disabled to prevent double-send
- morphdom will re-render the row on next SSE tick, resetting the button — acceptable

